										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026: Download Call Letter for Teaching &amp; Non-Teaching Posts</strong></p>
<p><strong>KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026:</strong> The Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) will soon release the KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026 for candidates who qualified in the Tier 1 examination. The admit card is expected to be available around March 24, 2026, a few days before the examination.</p>
<p>Candidates appearing for the Kendriya Vidyalaya Sangathan (KVS) and Navodaya Vidyalaya Samiti (NVS) Tier 2 Exam will be able to download their hall tickets from the official websites once released.</p>
<p>The Tier 2 examination will be conducted from March 27 to March 31, 2026, for various teaching and non-teaching posts including PGT, TGT, and PRT. Candidates must carry a printed copy of the admit card along with a valid photo ID to the exam centre.</p>
<h3>KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026 â€“ Overview</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Particular</th>
<th>Details</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Conducting Authority</td>
<td>Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Recruitment</td>
<td>KVS &amp; NVS Teaching / Non-Teaching Posts</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Posts</td>
<td>PGT, TGT, PRT and others</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Total Vacancies</td>
<td>15,762</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Admit Card Release Date</td>
<td>24 March 2026 (Expected)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Exam Dates</td>
<td>27â€“31 March 2026</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Mode of Exam</td>
<td>Objective + Descriptive</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Official Websites</td>
<td>cbse.gov.in / kvsangathan.nic.in / navodaya.gov.in</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026 Download Link</h3>
<p>The <strong>download link for the KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026</strong> will be activated <strong>2â€“3 days before the exam date</strong>, likely on <strong>March 24, 2026</strong>.</p>
<p>Candidates can download the admit card from the official portals:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cbse.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.cbse.gov.in</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.kvsangathan.nic.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.kvsangathan.nic.in</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.navodaya.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.navodaya.gov.in</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Once released, candidates must <strong>download and print the admit card immediately</strong> and verify all details mentioned on it.</p>
<h3>Details Required to Download Admit Card</h3>
<p>Candidates must keep the following login credentials ready:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Registration Number</strong></li>
<li><strong>Password</strong></li>
<li><strong>Security Pin / Captcha Code</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>How to Download KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026</h3>
<p>Follow these steps to download the admit card online:</p>
<ol>
<li>Visit the official website: <strong><a href="http://www.cbse.gov.in/cbsenew/recruitment.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.cbse.gov.in/cbsenew/recruitment.html</a></strong> or <strong>kvsangathan.nic.in</strong> or <strong>navodaya.gov.in</strong>.</li>
<li>On the homepage, find the link for <strong>Recruitment of Various Teaching &amp; Non-Teaching Posts in KVS &amp; NVS</strong>.</li>
<li>Click on the <strong>Admit Card / Call Letter</strong> link.</li>
<li>A login page will appear on the screen.</li>
<li>Enter your <strong>Registration Number and Password</strong>.</li>
<li>Fill in the <strong>Security Code</strong> and click on <strong>Submit</strong>.</li>
<li>Your <strong>KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026</strong> will appear on the screen.</li>
<li>Download the admit card and take a <strong>printout for exam day</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<p>If candidates forget their <strong>registration number or password</strong>, they can use the <strong>â€œForgot Registration Number / Passwordâ€�</strong> option available on the login page.</p>
<p><a href="https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5402.jpeg"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1315" src="https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5402.jpeg" alt="KVS NVS Tier 2 Admit Card 2026" width="1024" height="572" srcset="https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5402.jpeg 1024w, https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5402-300x168.jpeg 300w, https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5402-768x429.jpeg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<h3>KVS NVS Exam Schedule 2026</h3>
<p>The <strong>KVS NVS Tier 2 Exam 2026</strong> will be conducted from <strong>March 27 to March 31, 2026</strong> at various exam centres across the country.</p>
<p>The exam will be held for multiple posts including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Post Graduate Teacher (PGT)</li>
<li>Trained Graduate Teacher (TGT)</li>
<li>Primary Teacher (PRT)</li>
<li>Other Non-Teaching Positions</li>
</ul>
<p>Detailed <strong>post-wise exam schedule and shift timings</strong> will be mentioned on the admit card.</p>
<h3>Selection Process for KVS NVS Recruitment 2026</h3>
<p>The recruitment process includes the following stages:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Tier 1:</strong> Offline OMR-Based Examination (Pen &amp; Paper Mode)</li>
<li><strong>Tier 2:</strong> Objective + Descriptive Examination</li>
<li><strong>Skill Test / Interview</strong> (depending on the post)</li>
</ol>
<p>Candidates who qualify in all stages will be considered for final selection.</p>
<h3>Exam Day Instructions for Candidates</h3>
<p>Candidates must follow these guidelines on the exam day:</p>
<ul>
<li>Carry a <strong>printed copy of the admit card</strong>.</li>
<li>Bring a <strong>valid photo identity proof</strong> (Aadhaar, PAN, Voter ID, etc.).</li>
<li>Reach the exam centre <strong>well before the reporting time</strong>.</li>
<li>Do not carry <strong>mobile phones, calculators, smart watches, or electronic devices</strong> into the exam hall.</li>
<li>Follow all instructions mentioned on the <strong>admit card and exam centre guidelines</strong>.</li>
</ul>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
