<li>Visit the official website of India Post: <strong>indiapostgdsonline.gov.in</strong></li>
<li>On the homepage, click on the <strong>â€œGDS 2nd Merit List 2026â€�</strong> link.</li>
<li>Select your <strong>state or postal circle</strong>.</li>
<li>The <strong>GDS Merit List PDF</strong> will open on the screen.</li>
<li>Search your <strong>registration number or name</strong> in the PDF.</li>
<li>Download the file and take a <strong>printout for future reference</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<h3>India Post GDS Cut Off Marks 2026</h3>
<p>The <strong>GDS Cut Off Marks 2026</strong> will be released along with the merit list. The cut-off marks represent the <strong>minimum marks required to be shortlisted</strong> in the recruitment process.</p>
<p><a href="https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5401.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1303" src="https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5401.jpeg" alt="India Post GDS 2nd Merit List 2026" width="1024" height="572" srcset="https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5401.jpeg 1024w, https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5401-300x168.jpeg 300w, https://jobapply24.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_5401-768x429.jpeg 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<p>The cut-off may vary depending on several factors:</p>
<ul>
<li>Number of applicants in each state</li>
<li>Total vacancies available in the postal circle</li>
<li>Category-wise reservation rules</li>
<li>Overall <strong>10th class marks of applicants</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>As a result, <strong>cut-off scores differ for each state and category</strong> every year.</p>
