										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>RRB Paramedical Admit Card 2026 Released, Download Hall Ticket for CBT Exam</strong></p>
<p>The Railway Recruitment Board (RRB) has released the RRB Paramedical Admit Card 2026 on March 8, 2026 for candidates appearing in the upcoming Paramedical Categories Computer-Based Test (CBT).</p>
<p>Candidates who registered for 434 paramedical vacancies under Advertisement No. CEN 03/2025 can now download their E-Call Letter from the official regional RRB websites or the centralized portal.</p>
<p>The RRB Paramedical CBT exam will be conducted from March 11 to March 13, 2026 at multiple examination centres across the country. Candidates must carry their admit card along with a valid photo ID to the exam centre.</p>
<h3>RRB Paramedical Admit Card 2026 â€“ Key Highlights</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Conducting Body:</strong> Railway Recruitment Board (RRB)</li>
<li><strong>Exam Name:</strong> Paramedical Categories CBT 2026</li>
<li><strong>Advertisement Number:</strong> CEN 03/2025</li>
<li><strong>Total Vacancies:</strong> 434 Posts</li>
<li><strong>Admit Card Release Date:</strong> March 8, 2026 (Phased Release)</li>
<li><strong>Exam Dates:</strong> March 11, 12, and 13, 2026</li>
<li><strong>Exam Mode:</strong> Computer-Based Test (Online)</li>
<li><strong>Official Websites:</strong> rrbcdg.gov.in / rrb.digialm.com</li>
</ul>
<h3>RRB Paramedical Admit Card 2026 Download Link</h3>
<p>Candidates can access their admit cards through the official RRB portals.</p>
