<li>Carry a <strong>printed copy of the admit card</strong> to the exam centre.</li>
<li>Bring a <strong>valid photo ID proof</strong> such as Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Voter ID, or Passport.</li>
<li>Reach the exam centre <strong>at least 30â€“45 minutes before reporting time</strong>.</li>
<li>Electronic devices such as <strong>mobile phones, smart watches, and calculators are not allowed</strong> inside the exam hall.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Quick Tip for Candidates</h3>
<p>After downloading the admit card, carefully check all details. In case of any discrepancy, report it to the <strong>RRB support team within 24 hours</strong> to avoid issues on the exam day.</p>
